<%- include('partials/header', { title }) %>

<h1>LCA Analytics</h1>
<p>
  A read-only exploration of the U.S. Department of Labor's H-1B Labor Condition
  Application disclosures (FY<%= kpis.first_year %>–FY<%= kpis.last_year %>), normalised,
  classified, and entity-resolved by the LCA Normalization Engine.
</p>

<section class="kpi-grid">
  <div class="kpi-tile">
    <h3>Records</h3>
    <div class="big"><%= Number(kpis.total_records).toLocaleString() %></div>
    <div class="sub">Total LCA disclosures ingested</div>
  </div>
  <div class="kpi-tile">
    <h3>Classified</h3>
    <div class="big"><%= ((Number(kpis.classified_records) / Number(kpis.total_records)) * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</div>
    <div class="sub"><%= Number(kpis.classified_records).toLocaleString() %> with SOC code</div>
  </div>
  <div class="kpi-tile">
    <h3>Canonicalised</h3>
    <div class="big"><%= ((Number(kpis.canonicalised_records) / Number(kpis.total_records)) * 100).toFixed(2) %>%</div>
    <div class="sub"><%= Number(kpis.canonicalised_records).toLocaleString() %> linked to a canonical employer</div>
  </div>
  <div class="kpi-tile">
    <h3>Employers</h3>
    <div class="big"><%= Number(kpis.canonical_employers).toLocaleString() %></div>
    <div class="sub">Distinct canonical employers</div>
  </div>
  <div class="kpi-tile">
    <h3>Occupations</h3>
    <div class="big"><%= Number(kpis.distinct_socs).toLocaleString() %></div>
    <div class="sub">Distinct SOC codes</div>
  </div>
</section>

<h2 style="margin-top:32px">Pick your lens</h2>
<p class="muted">Each persona answers the questions that user actually asks of the corpus.</p>

<section class="persona-grid">
  <a class="persona-card journalist" href="/journalist">
    <h3>Journalist / Public →</h3>
    <p>Who sponsors the most H-1Bs? Where do they file? How has the volume moved year over year, and which occupations dominate?</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card jobseeker" href="/jobseeker">
    <h3>Job Seeker →</h3>
    <p>What's the prevailing wage for a role in a city? Which employers hire for a given SOC? How have wages drifted over time?</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card policy" href="/policy">
    <h3>Policy / Labor Economist →</h3>
    <p>Long-term trends — filings per year, wage growth by occupation, geographic concentration shifts, case-outcome distribution.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card academic" href="/academic">
    <h3>Academic / Methodology →</h3>
    <p>How the data was made: classification source mix, confidence distribution, entity-resolution layer outcomes, coverage stats.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card attorney" href="/attorney">
    <h3>Immigration Attorney →</h3>
    <p>Sponsor risk leaderboard — denial / withdrawal rates by employer, outcome trends year over year, cleanest high-volume sponsors.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card hr" href="/hr">
    <h3>HR / Compensation →</h3>
    <p>Wage benchmarking by SOC + state. P25 / P50 / P75 across the four DOL wage levels (I = entry → IV = senior).</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card economist" href="/economist">
    <h3>Economist / Macro →</h3>
    <p>NAICS sector evolution, top-10 SOC market concentration over time, real-terms median wage growth, sector rotation.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card investor" href="/investor">
    <h3>Investor / BI →</h3>
    <p>Hiring-signal leaderboards — which top-300 sponsors are scaling up vs pulling back, sector concentration, tech-SOC top sponsors.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card worker-rights" href="/worker-rights">
    <h3>Worker Rights / NGO →</h3>
    <p>Wages clustered nearest the legal floor, state employer-concentration risk, highest-withdrawal sponsors.</p>
  </a>
  <a class="persona-card student" href="/student">
    <h3>Student / Career Planner →</h3>
    <p>For a target SOC: entry → senior pay (Level I → IV), best-paying states, top hiring employers, year-over-year wage trend.</p>
  </a>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
